{"questionId":"14402","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following Venn diagram shows the events <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"B\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( A \\right) = 0.3\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>A</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.3</mn>\n</math></span>. The values shown are probabilities.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a008bd394f9889eb92d68a1a7059b92ce307a080.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1&nbsp;− (0.3 + 0.4), 1&nbsp;− 0.4&nbsp;− 0.1&nbsp;−&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;= 0.3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14402","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.S_1b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of q .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive,